  <description type="morphology">Plants to 4 dm; roots elongate, fleshily woody. Stems ± erect, usually branching. Leaves sessile; blade terete, to 7 cm. Inflores-cences cymose, much overtopping leaves; peduncle scapelike, to 20 cm. Flowers: sepals deciduous, ovate, 3–4 mm; petals pink to rose-purple, obovate, 9–15 mm; stamens (40–)50–100; stigma 1, subcapitate. Capsules subglobose, sometimes trigonous, 3–4 mm. Seeds without arcuate ridges, 0.8–1 mm. 2n = 24, 48.</description>
